The paper deals with the problem of maximizing the spread of influence in a social network, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The problem is modeled using graph theory and optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the threshold values attached to each vertex, which is a characteristic of social networks and could place it under the sub-category of social and economic networks (cs.SOC). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of approximation algorithms and fixed-parameter tractability, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
